day 3- Secure root SSH access
Solution
Step1: SSH into Each App Server
ssh <your-ssh-user>@<app-server-host>
Step2: Edit SSH Configuration
sudo vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config
Step3: find the below line
#PermitRootLogin yes
Step4: make it as follows
PermitRootLogin no
Step5: Save and exit (:wq in vi).
Step 6: Restart SSH Service
sudo systemctl restart sshd
Step 7: Verify the configuration
sudo sshd -T | grep permitrootlogin
Step 8: Expected output
permitrootlogin no
Step 9: Test SSH Access
ssh root@<app-server-host>
Step 10: Verify the below output
Permission denied, please try again.
